sections.heading: appropriators; declared first in right
sections.text: As between appropriators, the one first in time is first in right.SourceLaws 1889, c. 68, § 7, p. 504;R.S.1913, § 3371;Laws 1919, c. 190, tit. VII, art. V, div. 1, § 3, p. 832;C.S.1922, § 8408;C.S.1929, § 46-503;R.S.1943, § 46-203.AnnotationsThe right of approp
